Direct Known Subclasses:
ConvertNullTo, DMinMax, Equals, FmtBool, FmtDate, FmtNumber, ForbidSubStr, HashMapper, IsIncludedIn, LMinMax, NotNull, NullObjectPattern, ParseBigDecimal, ParseBool, ParseChar, ParseDate, ParseDouble, ParseInt, ParseLong, Required, RequireSubStr, Strlen, StrMinMax, StrNotNullOrEmpty, StrRegEx, StrRegExReplace, StrReplace, Token, Trim, Unique, UniqueHashCode
public abstract class CellProcessorAdaptor
extends Object
implements CellProcessor

Abstract super class for sharing behavior of all cell processors. Processors are linked together in a linked list. The end element of this list should always be an instance of NullObjectPattern. T denotes the type of information the cellprocessor is currently carrying.

Author:
Kasper B. Graversen
